Barely 24-hours, after suspected terrorists attacked a Kaduna-bound train, a few kilometres to the Kaduna metropolis, bandits, have attacked Gidan train Station along the Abuja-Kaduna rail track. Recall that on Monday night the train was attacked at about 7.45pm, leading to the death of no fewer than seven persons. Many also sustain injuries and some were kidnapped during the attack. However, Channels reports that the terrorists may have planted IEDs on the tracks forcing the train heading to Abuja from Kaduna to a stop. Meanwhile, President Muhammadu Buhari has said he is deeply pained by the sad development. According to him, he has issued a directive to security chiefs to hunt down the terrorists and rescue those abducted.